==Baekje==

===Etymology===
Probably inflecting stem {{IPAfont|*k(j)ə-}} + gerundive {{IPAfont|*-n}}, the latter being attested as {{cog|oko|隱|tr=*-n}}.

Connected to {{cog|okm|하다|하-|tr=ha-|t=to be many, to be great}}, {{cog|oko||*흐그-|tr=*huku-}} > {{cog|okm|크다|크〮-|tr=khú|t=to be large}}.

===Adjective===
{{head|pkc|adjective|tr=*k(j)ə-n|{{w|Nihon Shoki}}|琨|or|コニ|or|コ|f1nolink=1|f2nolink=1|f3nolink=1}}

# [[big]], [[great]]

====Reconstruction notes====
Attested as {{ltc-l|鞬}} in ''{{w|Book of Zhou}}'', as part of a compound word.

Attested primarily in compounds as {{m|ja||コニ|tr=*koni}} or sometimes {{m|ja||コ|tr=*ko}} in kana glosses to the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}''. {{m|ja||コニ|tr=*koni}} may be a transcription of {{IPAfont|*k(j)ə-n}} because Old Japanese lacked coda {{IPAfont|*-n}}, or alternatively a transcription of the sequence {{IPAfont|*k(j)ə-n i}} "the great one"; compare {{cog|okm|크〮니〮|tr=khún í|t=the great one}}. Also attested in the original text as {{ltc-l|琨}}. <!-- Source: https://nihonsinwa.com/page/1540.html -->

Perhaps also attested as {{ltc-l|近}}, an element in the titles of several Baekje kings: {{lw|ko|근초고왕|近肖古王|tr=Geun-Chogo-wang}}, {{lw|ko|근구수왕|近仇首王|tr=Geun-Gusu-wang}}, etc. These titles are also attested in forms that lack {{lang|zh|近}}, showing that it is a separate, detachable element.

